1.4 Five-year Accident History

MRD had one accident in the last 5 years covered by 40 CFR Part 68.42(a) in accordance with 40 CFR Part 68.168.  The incident occurred on September 12, 2019, and involved contract employees bolting up piping spool pieces to two 2-in valves on the discharge piping on the FCC main fractionator slurry pumps.  The bolts on the blind flanges of both 2-in tie-in valves were loosened to confirm there was no pressure.  Approximately one hour after bolt-up work began, a leak occurred on one of the valves, releasing approximately 523 barrels of hot FCC slurry, injuring 2 employees, and causing $250,000 in onsite property damage. Additional information is provided in Section 6 of the RMPlan.

1.5 Emergency Response Program Information

